# Planned Architecture

```
Keyboard Input
        │
        ▼
 Role Resolver
        │
        ▼
Performance State
      ╱   ╲
     ▼     ▼
Foundation  Voice
  Engine    Engine
     │        │
     ▼        ▼
Foundation   Voice
Transition   Transition
 Policy       Policy
      ╲      ╱
       ▼    ▼
     Output Merger
          │
          ▼
      MIDI Output
```

---

# Current Foundation Transition Policies

## TNC Pedal

Foundation transitions immediately.

Produces clearly articulated Foundation movement while allowing Voice to use the
selected Transition Mode and Transition Time.

Ideal for:

- Organ-style bass pedals
- Articulated bass lines
- Rhythmically defined Foundation movement

---

## TNC Smooth

Foundation transitions using a short overlap intended to engage glide without
producing a noticeable Foundation bloom.

Voice behavior remains unchanged.

Ideal for:

- Expressive synth bass
- Smooth bass movement
- Fluid lead playing over a moving Foundation

---

# Architectural Principle

The Role Resolver determines *what* each performer should do.

Each performer independently determines *how* to perform its assigned role.

Only after both performers have completed their work are their outputs merged
into the final MIDI stream.

Maintaining this separation of responsibility is fundamental to the long-term
extensibility and stability of the Tonic engine.
